# distribution of default's categories

default_labels = {0: 'No Churn', 1: 'Churned'}
default_counts.index = default_counts.index.map(default_labels)


plt.bar(default_counts.index.astype(str), default_counts.values, edgecolor='black')

plt.title('Number of Customers that Defaulted')
plt.xlabel('Defaulted? ')
plt.ylabel('Count')


plt.show()

In [108]:
dates = pd.DataFrame(fit_dat['enrolldt'])

dates['enrolldt'] = pd.to_datetime(dates['enrolldt'], format='%Y%m%d')
  
dates['month'] = dates['enrolldt'].dt.to_period('M').dt.to_timestamp()


sns.histplot(dates['month'], bins=30, kde=True, color='skyblue', edgecolor='black')


plt.title('Number of Customers Enrolling Over Time')
plt.xlabel('Month')
plt.ylabel('Total Enrollments')
plt.xticks(rotation=90)  
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
In [110]:
# proportion of gender given default type 
props = fit_dat.groupby(['default', 'gender']).size().reset_index(name='Count')
props['Prop'] = props['Count'] / props.groupby('default')['Count'].transform('sum')
props.head()

In [111]:
# proportion of gender given default type 
data = props.pivot(index='default', columns='gender', values='Prop').fillna(0)
data.index = data.index.map(default_labels)
data.columns = data.columns.map(gender_labels)


data.plot(kind='bar', stacked=False)
plt.title('Proportion of Gender by Default Type')
plt.ylabel('Proportion')
plt.xlabel('Default Type')
plt.xticks(rotation = 0)
plt.legend(title='Gender')
plt.show()

In [118]:
# seeing how many customers default given their enrollment month
dates['default'] = fit_dat['default']

grouped_dat = dates.groupby(['month', 'default']).size().unstack(fill_value=0)


grouped_dat.plot(kind='line')
plt.title('Customer Defaults By Enrollment Months')
plt.xlabel('Enrollment Month')
plt.ylabel('Number of Customers')
plt.xticks(rotation=45)
plt.legend(['No Churn', 'Churned'])
plt.grid()
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
